### 🚀 API Basics — TL;DR

**API** (Application Programming Interface):
A *set of rules* that lets different software apps communicate with each other — usually over the web using HTTP. ([Wikipedia][2])


SOAP (VERY OLD)
A protocol with strict standards and rules.
Uses XML only for messages.
Designed for formal enterprise web services.

REST (LATEST)
An architectural style (not a protocol).
Usually uses HTTP methods (GET/POST/PUT/DELETE).
Supports many formats like JSON, XML, plain text (JSON most common).

